    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "The reality, of course, is that it‚Äôs all about power."
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "h2",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "The power of the highly organised, highly political online"
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "Public social media, like Twitter, like Facebook, delivered highly organised ideological groups extreme power to make other people‚Äôs lives difficult. Occasionally, this is good. Often, this is bad. It‚Äôs not new, though. It dates back to "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            2
          ],
          1,
          "at least"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          " 2009:"
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      10,
      1
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "At some level, though, we have to acknowledge there‚Äôs a good reason that we don‚Äôt use angry mobs as a system of justice in most civilised parts of the world. It doesn‚Äôt seem like a great idea to make it a routine form of justice in the online world."
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "This is not a politically partisan point: once a gun is invented, it can be used to shoot anyone, both those we detest and those we admire. Online power does not respect politics, it only respects numbers and commitment."
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "h2",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "This is a discussion about use ‚Äî and abuse ‚Äî of power"
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      10,
      2
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "We‚Äôre on a dark path, and our discussions about it are woefully trivial right now."
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "Perhaps the only bit of good news that is that "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            2
          ],
          1,
          "finally"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          " our traditional systems of justice are beginning to work on online abuses. Alex Jones is on "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            3
          ],
          1,
          "the verge of bankruptcy"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          ". "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            4
          ],
          1,
          "Alex Belfield is in prison"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "."
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "(Probably some people not called Alex, too. But Alexes of the internet ‚Äî you‚Äôre on notice‚Ä¶ üòâ)"
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "But meanwhile, online, people continue to find new ways to exercise their new power. And we really, badly, need to have a conversation about how to manage that. And I have zero faith that the current ‚Äî or aspirational‚Äî social media platform owners are up to that."
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "How do we preserve social media‚Äôs ability to give voice and power to the powerless and the oppressed, while also curtailing the power of online mobs to ruin lives? That‚Äôs a much more interesting discussion than the highly loaded impossible question."
        ]
      ]
    ],
