          0,
          "Charles Arthur wrote a long piece following up on these ideas on his Substack:"
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "blockquote",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "However, this isn‚Äôt how Twitter functions. The prevalence of Angry Mobs essentially keyword-surfing to find things to be angry about is a serious problem. What makes it worse is that this sort of activity rewards obsessive people with too much time on their hands who REALLY WANT YOU TO KNOW THEIR OPINION, and why yours is wrong, as this is usually their reason for engaging with you. I‚Äôm sure you know what I mean: the tedious sealion who just won‚Äôt stop, who once you mute or block them, and take a look at their tweets, you find has moved on to the next person or "
